properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 7 at 10:42AM EST until February 7 at 5:00PM EST by NWS Key West FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest to north winds near 20 knots, will decrease to
near 15 knots. Seas as high as 7 to 10 feet, especially across
the Straits of Florida and the deeper waters surrounding the Dry
Tortugas will slowly subside.

* WHERE...Straits of Florida, Hawk Channel from Ocean Reef to
west end of Seven Mile Bridge, and Gulf waters beyond 5
fathoms including the Dry Tortugas.

* WHEN...In Effect.

* IMPACTS...A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 20
to 33 knots, or seas of 7 feet or greater, are expected to
produce hazardous conditions for small craft. These hazardous
conditions may result in poor vessel handling and steering
response, broaching, overturned dinghies and kayaks, slips and
falls on slippery decks, rub damage along docks and seawalls,
swamped bows at reef tract mooring balls, and dragging anchors.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced boaters, especially those with smaller vessels,
should avoid operating in these conditions.
